<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-10-29T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-10-29T05:00:00-05:00" n="438" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d438">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/6302:
                                    Telegram</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Reed</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss>
                                    </hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-10-29T12:00:00+02:00">October 29, 1940—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received October
                                        29—7:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>1033. The outbreak of hostilities with Greece has not yet been
                                    announced to the Italian people either in the press or on the
                                    radio. This morning’s press however carries the text of the
                                    Italian ultimatum and editorials declare that any resistance on
                                    the part of Greece will be overcome by the Italian Armed
                                    Forces.</p>
                                <p>Text of the note will be forwarded by mail.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reed</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>